caption: While I'm never a fan of a mandatory % of tip. The food was top notch! Reviews of the bone marrow burger didn't lie. Highly recommend!!!!
Very friendly to delivery.
Had great service, good whiskey selection let's go!
Great burger, excellent service 👌

It was my first time coming here! The spicy fried chicken sandwich is so yummy! My husband got the napa chicken sandwich and enjoyed it as well!  It wasn't busy when we went so barely had to wait.  Also if you like cocktails they have a refreshing one called Wild Child!
I got to try the vegetarian burger with sweet potato fries. everything was really good and the burger was divine.
Nice place. Very delivery friendly and well organized.
Funky robot ordering but great service and beer.
Bomb service and best chicken tenders in town! Highly recommend 👌

The food was delicious but they have a mandatory 16% gratuity I ask the waitress to ask the bartender for a sweet drink and he gave me a bitter sour drink with something spicy on the rim I don't do spicy what ever the special drink was the waitress was in attentive and forgot everything I had to ask for thing from the hostess because the waitress got lost
Great food and atmosphere! And Gabby was an awesome server!
Gabby was a great waitress! All the staff, drinks and food were amazing!
Good food but a bit too over priced. Also, a 16% gratuity is automatically added onto the bill.
As always, great service, fabulous food!!
Best burger I’ve ever had!
Eureka is always the best. Serving up undeniably delicious food and great cocktails. I recommend going for weekend brunch.
Good food good environment good service

Very cool environment! We walked in and had a 45 min wait but luckily 2 seats opened up at the bar so we snatched them up! Taylor was our server/bartender and she was fantastic! Super friendly and inviting- gave us recommendations that were out-of-this-world! Highly recommend the Brussels sprouts as a starter - I could’ve eaten that for my meal. We also got the bone marrow burger and the fig burger......if you are a goat cheese fan, definitely go with the fig burger! It was outstanding!! And the rum cake - don’t skip it!

Great burgers and beer selection. Service leaves something to be desired, but that is difficult to navigate with new all-digital menus and COVID-era dining. Get the bone marrow butter. You won't regret it.
We had the chicken cobb salad. Very good with lots of veggies. Friendly, helpful staff.
Great Burger and Fries!!!

Wow! I was just making a pit stop in Boise for food and fuel, and I was blown away by Eureka!  The bison burger was a combo of spicy and sweet that I was reluctant to try but it was amazing. Mac & cheese fried balls really really good too.  COVID-19: everyone spaced spaced far apart. Lots of hand sanitizer everywhere.

The food was hot and delicious. We dined outside, it was a beautiful day with warm space heaters. The mobile ordering was different at first but my husband and I picked it up quick. The server did tell us about the small service charge we were fine with it.
Not to bad pretty good would go here again.
Love the pick up table for pickups. Thank you. Postmates friendly.
Loved the food and cocktails!
Watermelon mint drink is amazing
I really enjoyed this place. Great good and great staff.

Eureka! is one of my favorite Boise restaurants with tasty food and friendly staff! They have many safety measures in place for visitor comfort - required masks, fully online ordering/payment, and plexiglass barriers between tables. Wonderful restaurant, I would highly recommend and will definitely return!

Super friendly staff, tasty food. Their COVID measures are extensive including not accepting cash for the bill and adding an automatic 16% service charge (aka tip) but our server definitely didn't slack in providing great service.

The burgers here are one of the highlights of the city. The staff is friendly, accurate with orders and do not tend to hover but make sure you are not ignored. Server had a great understanding of the available beer and their different notes of flavor. However I was not impressed with being surprised with a service charge based on percentage of my bill after completing my meal. I do understand times are hard and I would hate to see these doors closed but this fee should be disclosed on their digital menu, or by staff before ordering, definitely before being handed the check.
love this place!!!! one of the best restaurants around cant wait to eat here again mmmmmm
Great appetizers, shared several, braised riblets, 😋 No contact menu, which was cool and easy to use.

Restaurant is nice and the service is pretty good. Been going here for a while. Recent visit for lunch, had a few drinks and everything was satisfactory. Got the bill, and the waiter told me there was a 16% service fee! We were a group of 4 and there was absolutely no warning or any disclosure of the 16% "service fee". That is unacceptable and uncalled for. I feel like this was a switch and bait tactic. Needless to say they have lost me as a customer.
The Truffle Cheese fries were delicious. The burger was amazing too.

I didn't want to give too low of a rating, I'm not trying to hurt the business at all but google shows there being vegan options when there is only one option. Eureka shows up as one of the first options when you look up vegan places in Boise and it isn't very vegan friendly. I highly recommend going somewhere else, like bbq4life if you are vegan.

on my last day in downtown Boise took my niece and nephews decided on this place for lunch.  I really liked it because it was completely touchless and ordering through my phone was pretty simple.   excellent atmosphere, food was excellent and service was on-spot.   definitely a place to go while walking along 8th Street.
Food was excellent, highly recommend!
Delicious burgers! The first time we visited, they got my burger order wrong and the owner came out to apologize and gave me a gift card. They went above and beyond!

A nice location and comfortable atmosphere. The staff are friendly and helpful. The deviled eggs are great with a touch of horseradish and the lollipop corn dogs were a nice treat. The 28 day dry aged angus burger was excellent, moist and flavorful a real treat for a burger lover. recommend
great veg burger
Service was great. Covid Protocols were solid. Happy Hour apps were dynamite

Hadn't tried any new places in awhile and decided to give Eureka a go for my MIL's birthday dinner. There are some dietary restrictions in our group and we were interested in the beet burger (delicious and vegan). The contact less ordering was originally off putting but ended up working out well! Our food came fast. The online ordering made it easier to request food without certain ingredients. My only complaint is that I wish we could have tipped more. There is an auto 16% gratuity charge but I didn't see a place to tip more. We would have happily tipped 20%.

Had a wonderful experience today at Eureka today! Enjoyed the wonderful truffle fries and chicken sandwiches! Our server was a joy! I wish I could reminded her name but she looked and talked just like Kristen Bell! 10/10 recommend :)

Great burgers and wings. The mac and cheese balls are to die for. I had the Holly Smokes drink and it was amazing. We ate our food to fast to get a picture, but if your on the fence about this place don't be. Its worth stopping in.

The food was to die for! Everything was so great from the chicken strips to the burger but the biggest hit was definitely the pesto chicken sandwich. Probably the best thing we had while in Boise. If you are not tech savvy then you might have some difficulty as you have to scan a QR code to get to the menu and order online from your table because they are trying to go contactless. We went to a nearby restaurant the day before and they had their menu online but still had full service which went much smoother. They do add a 16% service fee on the bill which we didn’t quite understand until we saw a sign on the table in really small letters explaining that it was for the tip. That’s totally fine but just not quite communicated very clearly. The service was very friendly though, and they are glad to help if you have any problems. Definitely would recommend if in the area!

Great service, a chill atmosphere and AMAZING food! This time, my husband and I shared a variety of appetizers and sides... Riblets, wings, Brussell sprouts and sweet potato fries. Sooooooo delicious!
Do yourself a favor. Eat here.
Delicious and pet friendly on the patio. Veggie beet burger was great!

Went to eat at Eureka in downtown on Sunday. The staff was masked but was seating people too close, we requested a different table for distance. The server was named Zack and had a very casual demeanor. We asked him, “How is your day?” He responds, “well I’m here.” 😒 Once we were served, I opened my place setting to find a sticky and dirty steak knife. I let the server know, and he had a nonchalant attitude and said, “ Yeah, it’s really hit or miss.” 😳 he brings me a new silverware and AGAIN is sticky and dirty. He doesn’t come back out for 10mins which by then I had washed my hands and decided my hands were the best option at this point. Informed him about the silverware, he says sarcastically, “ yeah I wasn’t here last night to make sure it got done.” It’s a group effort of an establishment so his attitude might as well have been flipping me off. Once we got the check we saw a “service fee” of 16%. My friend and I contemplated just not tipping if they are just going to add on random charges. It wasn’t communicated to us until after he brings back our ticket and cards to tell us that the 16% was an automatic gratuity but that extra tips were appreciated. He didn’t bring a pen because of the current pandemic, yet he could serve me disgustingly dirty silverware, TWICE! This is the first time I have been at a sit down place since COVID and I’m appalled by my experience. Our order of riblets, sweet potato fries, brussel sprouts, and 2 cocktails ended up costing $60. Even without COVID this would definitely not be appropriate.
Bone marrow burger...... Wow

The place is great, the lonely star is for their aloha ordering system, it is trash,  why would you put your customers through that experience? The only reason we didn’t order more and didn’t stay longer is because it’s such a PIA to order anything. Whoever at Eureka thought it was a great idea to get that ordering system, this star is for you. Someone introduce this place to tabbedout ASAP!

Unorganized and poor handling of COVID as well as annoying customer service. We went in for dinner after looking at their online menu on their website. We went in and were told they were now doing “Contactless” ordering where you scan a code on your phone and order online and they bring it to you. Took forever to order and they only had half of their items on there which was disappointing. The waiters would not leave us alone and kept telling us how to use it. Also, when you order on the app, they add a MANDATORY “service charge” of $10.00 which is ridiculous considering our meal WOULD have only come out to $40-50 had we not finally walked out. Also why are you charging a service fee if you’re not even serving us. Just use a menu... and stop cutting your menu in half. If you’re not going to serve a certain dish take it off your website. Unhelpful and not worth the rather expensive prices anyways.

Ordered for delivery via doordash. First off I wish I had gone with fast food since the burger would have been better. This establishment is way over priced. $15 is way too much to pay for a mediocre burger that tastes no better than one from McDonald's. I also ordered a side of blue cheese to go with my sweet potato fries and got 3 packets of honey instead. Who dips fries in honey?! I tried it and it's disgusting. Thank you for assaulting my taste buds and my wallet.
Great food and service 🤗
I misunderstood the instructions I received and showed up an hour after my pick up time. The staff was nice enough to remake my order without hesitation. Great food and great customer service!

EDIT: Eureka is tumbling. The wife and I were so excited to finally be able to eat out again after the ridiculousness of COVID. After we were sat we were told about their new way of "Contact-less ordering". This alone turned out experience upside down. First off, the staff did not explain it very well. Not only did it take forever, its difficult to navigate and customize food.  It's not very specific and it takes the fun out of "Going out" IE... the wife wanted a beer, but the menu online has no options other than light beer/dark beer/malty/surprise me. She ended up getting frustrated  with the beer choices so she decided to go with a stiff drink. However, I had already submitted our order online at this point and now we would have to place a whole other order just to get a drink. This would require about 3 minutes on the phone to order another drink....again the wife said "forget it, they've made it too difficult". The staff also made it more difficult on themselves not accepting gift cards on the online platform. They had to redo our entire checkout process.  Second to note: The food seems to be going down hill. This was our favorite place to eat in all of the valley. However, it seems that the long COVID break broke the chefs for good. The nachos were lacking any sort of toppings and were incredibly bland. The chicken sandwich was overcooked - the chicken was chewy, dry and when you took a bite the entire chicken slid off of the sandwich because your teeth couldn't bite through it.  On a positive note the staff were always pleasant as usual.  All in all the date night was not very pleasant because of the reasons above. I don't know that we'll be going back anytime soon. They have pretty much killed the ambiance that once made eating out fun and an easy task.  Original Post: Oh gosh, where to start with Eureka....  There is something captivating about this place. It's not overly done in any particular way, but as soon as you walk in the door you're always greeted quickly, the drinks and the food are always made fresh and from scratch. The staff is always helpful and friendly. The people around you are always smiling, laughing and enjoying their visit. I've been here at least 30 or 40 times now and yet to have had a problem with anything. The staff here aspire to put out only the best it seems and it works! This is one heck of a restaurant that I suggest everyone tries at least once! Oh, and don't forget the mac n cheese balls.....

I really enjoyed my first visit here as the food was great. I decided to take my dad here, but as we entered they told us to take a seat and they would put on gloves. We sat outside at a table but apparently that one wasn’t sanitized even though we were the only people in the restaurant. We moved and were then informed their new policy was “no contact”. They wear gloves only to touch our plates/glasses and we use some complicated ordering system by scanning an icon with our phone. It wouldn’t work on my phone and the whole experience was just weird. We got up an ate down the street instead.
Before COVID this place was a staple for me.  Once they reopened their new ordering system was frustrating and didn’t make sense.

Ordered food to go with delivery via DoorDash. It was everyone in my party’s  first time trying Eureka. We ordered burger meals and the truffle fries.  The food was okay. Overpriced, especially considering I’ve had better burgers at Red Robin. The fries were decent.  My main reason for reviewing is the fact that our to-go bag came with a sticker reading, “Next time, put on some pants and dine with us.” Umm... What an odd thing to tell your customers. Perhaps somebody at Eureka thought that that sticker would be funny and witty. Myself and everyone in my party thought it was in poor taste.  I can’t imagine why an establishment would choose to be condescending to ANY customer, regardless of whether they dine in-house or order to go. When one factors in the pandemic and current recommendations to limit public outings, this choice seems especially tacky.  Not that it’s even REMOTELY your business, but pants were on when we ordered, thanks. I’m glad we had the chance to experience this mediocre offering between shifts at work. Our families come to Boise once or twice a year— now we know to leave Eureka off our list of dining recommendations.

My significant other and I just ordered from here through DoorDash, and wow the food was amazing!!! I definitely cannot wait to check this place out in person! We were both extremely beyond satisfied with the food we received !!!!

This place is incredible. I have been multiple times and the vibe and food is always great. They are doing a really good job of social distance.  So it's been a go-to for us the past few months. Tanner and Josh really made our July 4th dinner out a great experience for us!  Highly recommend the Napa Chicken Sandwich, sweet potato fries, lemonade, and Fresno Fig Burger. Menu items rotate occasionally.

Eureka! is one of the more consistent spots for service and food on 8th street in downtown Boise! They have a very creative seasonal drink menu and the food is seriously legit! They have a wide variety of menu items and everything that I have tried has been delicious.
Highly recommend the truffle fries!
Good place to hang out and have a beer or drink. Good food and atmosphere. Great staff.

I have had outstanding burgers here but have sometimes ordered the same and it was mediocre. Some of their appetizers are surprisingly underwhelming and unimaginative in terms of flavor. Their falafel bites, for example,which I’ve ordered twice taste more like a pile of starchy bean-mash than the deep fried, tzatziki-smothered goodness you’d expect at a restaurant like this.

Eureka! is one of the more consistent spots for service and food on 8th street in downtown Boise! They have a very creative seasonal drink menu and the food is seriously legit! They have a wide variety of menu items and everything that I have tried has been delicious. I totally recommend these guys, especially for happy hour!
Sat out on the patio in the nice weather. They turned on the heater for us because it was slightly chilly. Food was a little slow to come out but was really good.
Wonderful.
Enjoyed the bone marrow burger very much! Great service

Friendly and fast service.  The food was fantastic and they had lots of options.  I was very impressed by their beer menu, with an awesome selection of beers from some of the best craft brewers all over the country.  Will definitely be coming back the next time I am in town.  Prices were reasonable as well.
I've been here multiple times and have always enjoyed the food & the service. Last night I got the "Young and in love" cocktail and it tasted perfect on top of looking top notch!
Foood, drinks and service are phenomenal!
GREAT service, food is good but burgers are salty. Amazing atmosphere
Good burgers and great atmosphere

I haven't been there in a while, but it's still decent. However, got tricked into a dipping sauce for $2 extra dollars. 2 bucks, sure no big deal... but tell me! I hate this kind of tricks, so watch out. And management, don't make your waiter oversell. Let the customer knowingly choose.
Great food!
Love this place and all that it stands for. Fabulous food, drinks and staff!
Stopped in for Happy Hour. Good apps, esp. the Brussel Sprouts. Very good American whiskey list and cocktails. And a friendly staff who like to chat about said whiskey.
Some of the best "bar food" I have ever had. Chicken sliders, brussel sprouts, and sweet potato fries are so delicious!
Great burgers!
Pretty sweet place to hang out

Whether through a delivery attend or jog, should be able to guarantee the quality of food. Unfortunately, did not do so. The food is freaking and my tacos are completely falling apart. I have pictures. One of the cheeseburgers that I did not order is completely Omak. And I do not remember the menu stating a sesame bun. The other cheeseburger that I did order has no bun.lol jokes on me
Food is super over priced but good. The girl manager is super stuck up and rude.
Food was absolutely excellent, music and atmosphere was great. They had me pay $10 for a Moscow Mule, it was good but I feel like the price was high. Will definitely come back though :-)
Super cool place !
Some of the best French fries in Boise and good service. The cocktails are mediocre but they have a bunch of local beers.
Really good food and atmosphere.
Best server...John!
Great food and atmosphere! Highly recommend. Mainly just bar food.
I love this place. You must try the cocktail"Wild child" Omg!! Amazing

First time we went, slow service, but amazing food. Second time, amazing service and just as amazing food! The sweet potato fries are drizzled with honey and worth the upcharge. A favorite place now, and right next to freak alley--great to bring family to. Glad we tried it again!

We have been heading to Eureka since they opened and have never been disappointed. Tonight John blew it out of the park and took excellent care of us. We would have returned regardless, but now look forward to seeing if John is on shift as well. Thanks John!

Great food and service. One of the best meals I've had in town recently. The bison burger and chili will have me coming back very soon. Huge beer list. Our server, Dennis was fantastic and we'll for sure be asking for him on our next visit.

Girls' night HH new favorite. The "Industry Margarita" (tequila, pineapple, ginger, orange, cilantro) is amaZiNG! you just gotta love cilantro to groove on this one. A very refreshing drink, sadly not on the HH menu. HH food pleases, but I do wish there was one more healthy option on the menu.
Wonderful atmosphere and delicious food!
Good drinks chill vibe. More of a corporate vibe tho. Less unique than other places

Thanks to all who was working around 10pm on Jan 5th 2020 you guys are awesome the bees knees outstanding customer service and care .. special shot out to John he excelled in all things restaurant and service thanks for being you and for being educated in your work and kind in your heart
Best Bison burger in Boise

By chance, I ended up spending the bulk of my New Year's Eve at this place. Never been in before (although my wife has). The place is neither small nor large - it's the inbetween size, not cramped, but also not so large that it becomes sequestered into zones and impersonal. They have a good selection of microbrew beers and ciders, and the $5 happy hour appetizer plates we tried were pretty good (truffle fries and fried cauliflower) and priced right. We also got the classic American burger, which was also fairly good and cooked correctly. We sat at the bar which features square metal stools that are somewhere between OK and a little uncomfortable - but the bar staff we interacted with were all friendly and efficient despite being kinda slammed on a New Year's Eve, so I didn't mind it so much. I will go there again.

First time at Eureka. Excellent service by Kate. I tried the Lollipop Corndogs, and the Truffle Cheese Fries - both were well-prepared and tasted delicious. My wife thought the Hemp Bowl was absolutely wonderful - both because of the great taste and the emotional joy from eating healthy. Definitely try this place out.
Amazing, creative, joyride for your palate!!
Outstanding burgers and cocktails. Visit this place. It won’t disappoint.

A coworker won free appetizers for his office, so we checked it out last night. They asked which free appetizers we wanted and we all got a different one so we could share and try them all. Food was good, but after we ate they said we had exceeded the limit and had to pay for some of the appetizers. No one had mentioned a limit previously, we hadn't ordered a lot for the number of people there, and everyone bought drinks. It's pretty shady to change the cost after someone eats.  I doubt any of us will go back.

Unique food pairings that work well together. Delicious and innovative cocktails. Friendly staff. The only reason I don't give 5 stars is because it is difficult to accommodate special diet here. Dishes that would initially thought to be suitable for special diets had special ingredients that make it tough to order without modifying. While the ingredients are delicious, it made it tough for gluten free, vegan, and vegetarians to order.
Great beers, food and people. This is a fun place to hang and relax.
Happy hour misleading and dood was ok.

I've been reluctant to order food from here because the burgers are a little pricey but oh man I finally decided to order one today and that was the best burger I've had in Boise hands down. Will definitely order from here again.
Very good food, great choices of beverages and they treated us like  we were valuable to them...
Great food and service
Love this place for it's atmosphere and wide range of food and drinks!
Food was great and the dessert was heavenly I forgot the name of it but it had bourbon in it.  Service was wonderful!!
Cozy, lively, atmosphere! Friendly bartenders, great beer selection! Will def have to try their food soon!

Best burgers! The bone marrow burger is amazing and the 28 day dry age burger is phenomenal. Two of the best burgers I’ve ever had, can’t choose between them. Eureka employees were extremely friendly and genuine.
The food is delicious and I enjoy their variety of drinks
Boooo

Awful experience. I've never sat at a restaurant's bar and not even been acknowledged. We sat there for 20 minutes, the bartender kept looking at us then would look away. Very weird. The restaurant was not busy at all, or else I might've understood better. We left after this experience. We tried it again a few months later and the food was sub par. Won't be back!

ABSOLUTELY LOVED MY EXPERIENCE. Start to finish, I was met with friendly faces and great conversation. Our server, Cindy, was no exception. She was helpful and knowledgeable when I had questions. Not to mention, we were there with a 6-month old but our experience was seamless. The bone marrow burger and brussel sprouts are must haves. I've never had a burger as good as the bone marrow burger. Seriously.
I have ate there a few times. Just not a fan
Had to wait half an hour before being seated but it was understandable! Excellent food and service 🙂🙂😄
Solid drinks and fried mac and cheese balls

Food and service is always amazing. If you've never been I strongly suggest their Wings, and ask to split the wings into the two sauces they have. Both are amazing. Tons of Beer on tap, and you usually will always get the manager on duty personally helping the staff out.  10/10 one of my go to spots for downtown
Great Happy Hour.  Excellent service. Tap beer selection large enough to please everyone.  The Chicken Nachos are really really good!
The food is amazing. Fun twists on classic dishes. Highly recommended.
Great service. Excellent food. Unique menu items. I got the fried Mac n cheese balls.
Great food and drink, wonderful atmosphere
Very noisy but the food and service were great!
Amazing food, amazing people and you just feel good when you're there
The drinks are great!

This is one of the few cool places I'm comfortable taking my kids for dinner.  Within minutes of sitting down, we had crayons, an activity sheet, and a bacon bloody mary.  Something for everyone!  They even have a tiny carrot-stick-and-watermelon-cube hors d'oeuvre plate that they bring out to keep the kids happy while waiting for your food. Smart.  The place was busy when we were there (Saturday at 5pm) and the service was prompt and attentive. I'll definitely be back next time for an evening out with the whole family.
so yummy! everyone is so kind and friendly!
Great bourbon
Ate here today and was not remotely disappointed. The food was great, the atmosphere was great, and the service was great too.
Choices of good beer limited. Food is decent. Very loud.
Very comfortable. Our waiter, Alex, very good, relaxed, which conveyed the feel of the place. Enjoyed lunch in a warm atmosphere. We'll go again!

Great atmosphere.  Sat at the bar and had awesome service and good conversation with the bartenders.  Everything is local and there is a great beer and whiskey selection.  The food and cocktails are delicious.  Bartenders are very knowledgeable.
One of our family favorites! Delicious food, always fresh. The Truffle fries are a must every time!

Been here 7-8 times since moving back to Boise three years ago, and it has been five stars every time.  Our waiter last night was Jon, and he was another example of exceptional service.  He had great suggestions, came by with just the right frequency, and was wonderful to talk to.  The food is always outstanding, with a unique twist on every dish.  Your only problem is being able to find time to go back and try everything on the menu.
Seriously, this place is the highlight of my foodie year. I loved everything. Can everything be my new favourite? Stoked on the awesome daily happy hour(s), too. $5 Apps? Yes, please.
Ordered a burger (medium) from Eureka! last night via DoorDash. It arrived rare at best. Won't be going back.
Long wait for food!
Macaroni balls are amazing
Excellent service & food.
Strange but extremely satisfying
Visited for brunch and it had a great selection, delicious sweet potato fries and burgers!
Great food and service
The server made perfect recommendations based on thing we said we liked, good selection of beer and menu items.

Went here while in town for business. Stopped in to get take out and have a beer. After waiting for 45 mins and 3 beers in the new waitress realized she didn’t get my order in. She was very apologetic and ended up not charging me for my food and gave me $20 gift certificate to come back for my inconvenience. Was expecting that and was very appreciative her handling of the situation. Now for the food...it was amazing. Highly recommend the bone marrow burger. Best hamburger I’ve ever had. So juicy and delicious. The Brussels sprouts were amazing along with the truffle fries. I will definitely come back next time I’m in town.
Delicious food and friendly people. Great selection of beer and whiskey
Food was delcious and their rib eye was the best steak I've ever eaten. Our server Jon was extremely educated about the food and drink menus and gave us fantastic recommendations. Highly recommend.
Great service, drinks and appetizers!

There were about 10 employees wandering around and hanging out at the POS station, and still took about 30 minutes till we ordered food, another 20 for the food to come out, and then the chicken on our salads was freezer burned & rubbery. Just bad service and bad food.
A little pricey, but the food and drinks were worth it.

The food was good and but the service was alright. John was our original server and he was amazing. Although we transferred sections because we were expecting more people, John went out of his way to continue to check on us and ensure that we were still having a good time and receiving great service. Thanks again John!

I visited Eureka! on a Friday for lunch and the server took forever to come out to greet us and ask for drinks. It was a warm day so I could have used as much water and iced tea as possible! This is why I give them a 4. Account for an 1-1/2 hour dining experience and you will be fine. Otherwise, the server was friendly, the food was top notch, and I will be going again. This is a hipster restaurant and vegan options are available.
Nice atmosphere.  Delicious food.

Jeff, amazing. Food, amazing. Atmosphere on the patio with my son, amazing. Just look at these beautiful drinks! Food for the eyes as well as the taste buds. We shared the Fresno Fig and Cowboy burgers. Both were delicious but the Fresno Fig was our favorite. My son loves sweet, so the sweet potato fries with honey drizzle floated his boat. Regular fries did it for me. Definitely go to Eureka!
Goof food, great beverage list. Service is usually good.
really good service here!!
Everything we've tried here we've enjoyed! Specifically the brussel sprouts, the bourbon cake, Mac & cheese balls, and good coffee too!  Definitely a fav.
Very nice bar and patio but I need to rave about the charcoal lemonade ! What ?! I've never had such a refreshing perfect lemonade !
Good food. Good staff

This place was totally an audible call by my in-laws for my birthday night out.  We cancelled reservations at a more up-scale restaurant in order to (I’ll be honest) wear shorts & a tank top in 94 degree heat! The HH menu at Eureka is fabulous!  Seared Brussel sprouts, lollipop corn dogs, spicy osso buco riblets and mac n’ cheese balls... SPOT ON with their drinks and burgers as well.  Our wait staff was extremely happy, helpful and patient with our (less than sober) rambling orders.  Great experience in Boise!

We first sat outside since it was a warm afternoon but soon ASKED for a seat indoors because there were so many flies. The food was OK but not great. There are many places around there and would try one if those if I did it again.
The 28 day aged burger was the best and so was the Kentucky mule.
I've been there about 4 times and 3 times my order has been messed up or given away to the wrong person. 😕 I would not reccomended this place to my worst enemy.
Had a great Burger and the was staff was on the ball with refills and services
You gotta go here..great service and bar service too. Knows how to make a great sidecar!
Great bartender!!
Great sandwiches and pizza

Came for a date night, great drinks and good food. Husband had the marrow burger and I had the beet burger (pictured). I have tried about half of the items on the menu and all of the appetizers and have only had one thing I didn't care for. The hemp bowl is my favorite entree, and my husband loves the jalapeno egg burger. It is worth going to try their food just because of all the different options they have that are exciting and so different than other restaurants.  Eureka is really something special.

Just got off a long plane ride with my son and wanted to go downtown to eat and look around. Saw these great reviews and knew I couldn't go wrong with a bison burger.  Went with the cheese fries + truffle dipping sauce for an appetizer and my son found a chicken strip dinner of kids menu.  The fries were good, and my son had no complaints. Needless to say, i didn't enjoy my bison burger.  The bun was cool to the touch (like it was refrigerated??). I asked our waiter if this was intentional and he went to kitchen to ask and he let me know it was not and that they would heat the buns if i wanted.  I don't make a habit of sending food back to the kitchen so I didn't go with that offer I just endured my cold bun burger.  The next thing was I had to pull my red onions off.  I expected them to be grilled with no structure remaining but after taking a couple of crunchy onion bites they had to go.  The other strange thing was there seemed to be 2-3 salt pockets within the meat of burger as ifi meat and spices weren't mixed long enough??  I did opt for the fried MacNcheese bites, instead of fries and I'll say neat concept but not for me.  Reading a couple of reviews I see there is a fan base though.  The host and waiter were very nice and attentive (4PM on a Wednesday so there was only a table of 8 besides us there) so that was a plus.  Also, the atmosphere and location were good.  I'm sure I got a rara bad experience with my bison burge, especially after seeing all the other five 🌟 reviews but can't say I'll be back.  Theres just too many other places to eat downtown.
